						               													<description>In &amp;quot;The Tournament&amp;quot; of Dungeons &amp;amp; Procrastination, you play as an enchanter participating in a summoning tournament. The arena's stands are packed with spectators!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Estimate the power of the opponent's summons in a tense face-off and cast a support summons if necessary, or would you rather bluff your way through a stunt? &amp;#10;That's when the dice are rolled, these 6-sided artifacts will grant your team its full power! &amp;#10;Which of the enchanters will win this tournament? &amp;#10;During each round, you must discard your opponent's cards and place them in your &amp;quot;Champions&amp;quot; pile with the highest score.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A round consists of 5 phases:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     The Duel&amp;#10;     Summoning Support &amp;#10;     Artifact Throwing (Dice) &amp;#10;     Combat Resolution &amp;#10;     End of Round &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;During this rounds each player will secretly choose a card from their hand as fighter and may add a support. Each card have a value and a special effect that can lead to victory!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Then each player will roll a 6-sided die and add the value of the die to their card score.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If a player has played a Support card during the round they will roll an additional die and add the value of that die to their score.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player with the highest value sends the opponent's card(s) to their &amp;quot;Limbo&amp;quot; pile, knocked out, face down. They places their winning cards in their &amp;quot;Champions&amp;quot; pile, face up.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Then each player draw a card of their deck and adds it to their hand.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends when a player has no more cards to play at the beginning of a round.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player with the most cards in their Champions pile wins the game!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
